About
This luxurious waterfront district adjacent to the Palm Jumeirah is lined with glittering skyscrapers, exclusive residences, and breezy boulevards that are entirely man-made.

The area

Neighborhood: The Marina
Its hard to believe that only a decade ago there was no marina. Opened in 2003, the man-made marina runs along a 3km stretch of shoreline. A heady mix of luxurious hotels, apartment buildings, and cafes, the marina hosts regular community events and markets, and is a wonderful place to while away an afternoon or evening. Spectacular at night when the skyscrapers glisten, here you can enjoy dinner on the beach next to the sea, or visit a high-rise bar in a hotel for a magnificent view across the Gulf and the man-made Palm Island, with the world-famous Atlantis Hotel at its end. The Walk at Jumeirah beach Residences is a pedestrianized stretch leading to a new development: The Beach. Its one of the few places where Gulf nationals mix with tourists and Western ex-pats. Its a popular place to show off your supercar for an evening, so watch out for Lamborghinis, Maseratis, and Ferraris in abundance.

    Lovely area but be on the look out
    A beautiful area to walk around either in the day or night, but the lights make the evening experience a little more enjoyable. Loads of smart restaurants and cafes to eat and drink at and not too expensive for the area. Just two issues that we didnt enjoy which stops me giving it 5 stars 1/ Some of the touts trying to get you to eat in their restaurant were a bit invasive and stopped a nice leisurely walk. Others are not a problem when you say you have eaten or meeting someone. Just be prepared! 2/ the second issue was a real nuisance and that is the E scooters that plague the area. They travel at some speed and you cant here them, they also have electric buggies that are a nuisance as well. I get that it would be beneficial for people with mobility problems but this is just for fun. Please be aware of your environment as there a few near misses. Personally Id like to see them stopped as it stops you relaxing as you walk about. Some fabulous yachts in the marina to drool over as well. There is also the marina mall which is pleasant to walk around

Dubai Marina is a vibrant and upscale district in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. It features a man-made canal city with a waterfront lined by high-rise residential and commercial buildings. The Marina is known for its luxurious lifestyle, with attractions such as the Marina Walka promenade offering shops, restaurants, and cafesand the Marina Mall. Its also home to various attractions like the Dubai Marina Yacht Club and offers stunning views of the citys skyline. The area is a popular destination for both residents and tourists seeking entertainment and relaxation.
